<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Not To Apply for Security Council Seat </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105163394 Stockholm Radio Sweden in English 1615 GMT 11 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1105163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm Radio Sweden </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Swedish radio news has learned that Sweden will not 
apply for a seat in the United Nations Security Council in 1995. 
It says Foreign Minister Margaretha af Ugglas will address the 
Swedish parliament on Monday [16 May]. She is expected to say 
that Sweden will not have enough support from the other member 
countries because among other reasons it is going against 
Germany and Italy. Sweden applied earlier in 1992, but lost out 
to New Zealand. 

</TEXT>

