<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Notes Denktas `Inconsistency' on Solution </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Notes Denktas `Inconsistency' on Solution </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1105113794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1105113794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktas now says that a 
federal solution in Cyprus is not possible because of the 
difference in views between the Greek Cypriots and Turkish 
Cypriots. Denktas, who is on a private visit to Turkey, called 
on the Turkish National Assembly to declare the union between 
the occupied areas [northern Cyprus] and Turkey on the same day 
the announcement is made that Cyprus has joined the European 
Union. Denktas asked the Turkish leadership not to confine 
itself to the military occupation, but to support the 
pseudostate financially. With financial support, he said, the 
pseudostate could become a showcase for Turkey, which will rid 
it of the image of an occupation force. 
  Alternate government spokesman Spiros Arotis stressed 
Denktas' inconsistency and recalled that the high level 
agreements [of 1977 and 1979] providing for a federal solution 
in Cyprus bear his signature. The spokesman said Denktas has 
proven in practice that what he seeks and hopes for eventually 
is the recognition of his pseudostate. 

</TEXT>

