<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Calls For End to Yemen Conflict </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Calls For End to Yemen Conflict </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1105152694 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1420 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1105152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, May 11 (A.A.) -- Turkey on Wednesday [11 
May] expressed concern about the political crisis in Yemen and 
about the chance that it might take the shape of armed clashes. 
  Foreign Ministry spokesman Ferhat Ataman said at his weekly 
briefing that Turkey calls for the Yemeni leaders to stop the 
conflict in harmony with their people's hope for unity and 
peace, and wishes that further bloodshedding would stop for the 
good of the country. 
  `During this critical stage which is going on in the 
country, 
Turkey calls for moderation between the two sides and hopes for 
an agreement to be reached as soon as possible,' Ataman said. 

</TEXT>

