<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Urges Backing for European Membership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Urges Backing for European Membership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1105141994 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1346 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1105141994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- According to President Boris 
Yeltsin, Russia wants to become a "member with equal rights" of 
all European institutions. Immediately before the start of his 
talks with Chancellor Helmut Kohl, Yeltsin told journalists that 
he hoped to get the chancellor's support for this. Yeltsin 
announced that a new era of reconciliation will begin between 
the two nations after the Russian troops depart. 
  Kohl welcomed Yeltsin as a "friend of our country and our 
people." With reference to the dramatic changes in the world, 
he said it is now important for Russia and Germany to make the 
correct decisions with prudence and far-sightedness. He also 
expressed the hope that the reforms in Russia will be successful 
under Yeltsin's leadership. Kohl emphasized that there have 
been terrible but also great chapters in the history of the two 
states. They must learn from both the bad and the good things. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

