<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Balladur Addresses National Assembly on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Balladur Addresses National Assembly on Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Urges Release of Aid Workers </H4>

<F P=102> LD1105165794 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1600 
GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1105165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Edouard Balladur has said he does not believe it is 
France's job to shoulder endlessly the duties and 
responsibilities concerning Bosnia that others reject. The 
prime minister, who was addressing the National Assembly this 
afternoon, added that the time for making a choice is 
approaching and that everyone must be aware of it. He demanded 
the unconditional release of the 11 French people in the 
organization Premiere Urgence who are still being held by the 
Bosnian Serbs. 

</TEXT>

