<H3> <TI>   Kinkel, Yeltsin Discuss European Security Structure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kinkel, Yeltsin Discuss European Security Structure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1305093094 Hamburg DPA in German 0814 GMT 13 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1305093094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn -- At the end of his visit to Bonn, Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin met Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel on 
Friday [13 May]. Diplomatic circles report that the problems of 
an all-European security structure were at the center of the 
talks held at the government's guest house near Bonn. 
  Kinkel had said before the meeting that Bonn and Moscow have 
also made some progress on the question of returning German 
cultural assets taken to Russia during World War II. 
  After the talks, Yeltsin traveled to Baden-Wuerttemberg on 
the last leg of his journey. Talks with Minister President 
Erwin Teufel and representatives of industry in Stuttgart and 
Ludwigsburg will focus on the deepening of economic relations. 

</TEXT>

