<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Bonn -- The Federal Government wants Bonn to be 
the headquarters of the new World Trade Organization (WTO) that 
is to succeed GATT in January 1995. The cabinet adopted 
Economic Minister Guenter Rexrodt's proposal on Wednesday [11 
May]. The offer was transmitted to the GATT Secretariat in 
Geneva immediately. The deadline for applications is 18 May. 
If the application is successful, the new institution will be 
understood as a compensation to Bonn for the government and 
parliament's move to Berlin. [passage omitted] 

