<F P=103> AU0905144694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Munich (DPA) -- Christian Social Union [CSU] 
Chairman Theo Waigel rejected the call of Social Democratic 
Party of Germany [SPD] Federal Manager Guenter Verheugen for an 
action alliance against the Republikaner by calling it an 
"obvious propaganda proposal." As long as the SPD only deals 
with right-wing extremists, but not also with left-wing radicals 
and the Party of Democratic Socialism [PDS], the CSU does not 
see a basis for a joint course of action, Waigel said before 
journalists after a session of the CSU Executive Committee in 
Munich. Moreover, the CSU does not need an exhortation. Unlike 
any other party, it is struggling against the Republikaner 
"politically and with all legally available means." 

</TEXT>

