<H3> <TI>   Maroni Names Claudio Gelati Cabinet Chief </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Maroni Names Claudio Gelati Cabinet Chief </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1305100994 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1248 GMT 12 
May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1305100994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Maroni Names His Chef de Cabinet"] </F>
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, May 12 -- Prefect Claudio Gelati, 55, 
was today named chef de cabinet at the Interior Ministry by 
Minister Roberto Maroni, who confirmed Gelati at the post he was 
moved to earlier this year by former Interior Minister Nicola 
Mancino. 
  Before taking on the portfolio with his swearing in 
yesterday, Maroni said he intended to keep on the job the senior 
civil servants who had been managing the affairs of the 
ministry's departments. 
  Still to name are the officials who usually become the 
minister's closest aides, the chief of the secretariat, the 
personal secretary and the head of the ministry's press office. 
  The chef de cabinet served earlier, at the end of last year, 
as special commissioner for Milan when the great northern city 
was temporarily without a mayor. 

</TEXT>

