<H3> <TI>   Euroelections Poll Shows Forza Italia, AN, PDS Growth </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Euroelections Poll Shows Forza Italia, AN, PDS Growth </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0605150294 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1401 GMT 6 
May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0605150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Voter Survey on June 12 Elections"] </F>
  [Text] Rome 6 May (ANSA) -- Forza Italia, National Alliance 
[AN] and two left-wing opposition parties, the Democratic Party 
of the Left [PDS] and Communist Refoundation [Communist 
Renewal], will all gain votes in the June 12 European Parliament 
elections compared to the March 27 general elections, according 
to a CIRM [Italian Center for Market Research] survey released 
Friday [6 May]. 
  The poll results, to be published in the next issue of the 
news weekly, L'ESPRESSO, show that Silvio Berlusconi's Forza 
Italia party would obtain 24.2 percent of the vote, compared to 
21.1 percent in March, while its neo-Fascist government partner, 
National Alliance, would increase its votes by 1.1 percent. 
  The Northern League on the other hand would drop 1.1 percent 
compared to the previous elections, CIRM said. 
  The Left democrats would increase their votes by 1.4 percent 
and Communist Refoundation by 0.9 percent, according to CIRM, 
which did not say how it was able to separate the parties, both 
right and left, which in the March elections were running under 
the same ticket. 
  The opposition Greens would remain stable while the Pact for 
Italy would lose 0.8 percent and the former Christian Democrats 
of the People's Party would lose 0.5 percent. The Pannella 
Ticket, too, would drop by 1.5 percent. 

</TEXT>

