<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "CARIPLO, June 6 Capital Hike Before </F>
Market Launch"] 
  [Text] Rome 6 May (ANSA) -- The Milan-based commercial bank 
CARIPLO [Lombard Provinces' Savings Bank] plans a capital hike 
from 3.5 trillion to 4.5 trillion lire to be voted at a 
shareholders meeting on June 6, the agenda published today 
indicated. 
  The capital increase is planned in two tranches, the second 
of which to be a warrant bond issue. 
  The assembly is expected to vote the stock market launch of 
CARIPLO shares at that meeting, according to the agenda outlined 
by the bank's new president Sandro Molinari. 

