<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Confidence-Building Measures Talks Continue in Vienna </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Confidence-Building Measures Talks Continue in Vienna </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1205160994 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1500 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1205160994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The talks on the confidence-building measures 
[CBM's] continue in Vienna. Gustave Feissel, the UN secretary 
general's alternate special representative, continued the talks 
with Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktas' envoys in the presence 
of Robert Lamb, the U.S. State Department special coordinator on 
the Cyprus issue, and Tugay Ulucevik, the Turkish deputy foreign 
minister. 
  Lamb told the Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation that he and 
Ulucevik were just observers in the talks. He added that 
today's talks focused on a detailed analysis of the 21 March UN 
document. He avoided evaluating the talks' results. 
  The talks began at 1030 today, stopped at 1500 and resumed 
at 
1600. 
  Acting government spokesman Spiros Arotis said nothing 
happened in yesterday's seven-hour talks. He added that the 
government is being kept informed. 

</TEXT>

