<H3> <TI>   Turkish Cypriots Sign Tourism Pact With Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Cypriots Sign Tourism Pact With Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1205132294 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 0959 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1205132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Lefkosa [Nicosia], May 12 (A.A.) -- The Turkish 
Republic of Northern Cyprus, upon which an embargo is imposed, 
made an agreement with Israel to boost tourism, a move that 
would eventually give impetus to the country's economy. 
  Scheduled maritime travel between Gazimagosa [Famagusta] Bay 
and the Haifa Bay in Israel has been established on a regular 
basis. 
  Sea buses of the Fergun Navigation Company have been 
conducting trial cruises since March. [passage omitted] 

