<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Athens Warned on Extending Territorial Waters </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Athens Warned on Extending Territorial Waters </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1205161694 Ankara ANATOLIA in French 1550 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1205161694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, 12 May 1994 (A.A.) -- Foreign Ministry 
spokesman Ferhat Ataman declared on Thursday [12 May] that 
Athens' desire to extend its territorial waters to 12 nautical 
miles is unacceptable. 
  Until 1936, Greece had limited its territorial waters to 3 
miles. After the Montreux Convention on the straits, it extended 
its territorial waters to 6 nautical miles. 
  Turkey claims that Athens' extension of its territorial 
waters to 12 nautical miles will be considered a declaration of 
war. 
  Greek Foreign Ministry spokesman Konstandinos Bikas [name as 
received] affirmed that it is Greece's sovereign right to extend 
its waters to 12 nautical miles. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

