<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Central Bank Discloses Jan-Feb Foreign Debts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Central Bank Discloses Jan-Feb Foreign Debts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1205153494 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1510 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1205153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, May 12 (A.A.) -- Turkey's foreign debts 
return payments for January and February 1994 totalled 1.87 
billion U.S. dollars, it was announced on Thursday [12 May]. 
  According to the Central Bank's payment balance sheet, 613 
million dollars were paid in capital and 474 million dollars for 
interest. 
  This amount for the same period last year was 581 million 
dollars in capital and 399 million dollars for interest for a 
total of 980 million dollars. 
  According to this data, Turkey paid 10.9 percent more in 
foreign debts compared to the same period last year. 
  In capital payments, 318 million dollars were made in the 
public sector, 47 million dollars in the trading banks, and 248 
in various other sectors. 
  As for interest payments, 292 million dollars were made to 
the public sector, 149 million dollars in trading banks and the 
private sector, and 33 million dollars to State Economic 
Enterprises. 
  Foreign capital in Turkey has decreased by 42 percent 
compared to the same period last year, falling to 40 million 
dollars. 
  In 1993 this amount was 69 million dollars. 

</TEXT>

