<H3> <TI>   Transaction Deficit Increases </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Transaction Deficit Increases </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1205152794 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1450 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1205152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, May 11 (A.A) -- Turkey's current 
transactions deficit for January and February increased by 57 
percent compared to the same period last year, it was announced 
on Thursday [12 May]. 
  According to the `balance sheet' released by the Central 
Bank, the deficit for the year's first two months amounted to 
701 million U.S. dollars. This amount was 446 million dollars 
in 1993 for the same period. 
  However the foreign trade deficit has declined by 75 million 
dollars compared to the same period last year from 1.35 billion 
dollars to 1.275 billion dollars. 

</TEXT>

