<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Visit Confirms Good Relations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Visit Confirms Good Relations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1305113694 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1007 GMT 13 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1305113694 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- According to government spokesman 
Dieter Vogel, Russian President Boris Yeltsin's visit to the 
Federal Republic, which ends today, confirms the good and 
cooperative relations between the countries both in its course 
and its outcome. The Russian side appreciated Germany's efforts 
to include Russia in the West's security and economic 
cooperation, Vogel said in Bonn today. Russia's inclusion in 
NATO's Partnership for Peace initiative is already "well under 
way," and the extension of the leading G-7 industrial countries 
to include Russia will continue, initially politically and later 
economically. 
  The issue of bidding farewell to the [Russian] troops, on 
which there has been heated public debate in both countries, was 
one problem that was "speedily resolved in the spirit of mutual 
understanding." Before a cultural function in Weimar there will 
now be an official farewell ceremony for the troops in Berlin. 

</TEXT>

