<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Group Claims Responsibility for YSEE Car Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Group Claims Responsibility for YSEE Car Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1205125294 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1130 GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1205125294 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At dawn today unidentified people set fire to a car 
belonging to the YSEE [Greek General Confederation of Labor] in 
Aryiroupolis. The car, which was parked at the junction of 
Trapezounda and Olimbia Streets, was destroyed. The 
Revolutionary Violence Cells [Pirines Epanastatkis Vias] claimed 
responsibility for the car's arson in a telephone call to a 
private radio station. 
  A YSEE statement described the arson as a provocative action 
aimed at disorientating the working people. The statement 
condemned the unseen elements, who, with their suspicious and 
evil presence, have again tried to open a front against the 
trade unions--and this on the day of the May Day observances. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

