<H3> <TI>   Dutch Minister Calls For Humanitarian Aid to Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dutch Minister Calls For Humanitarian Aid to Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1605090594 Hilversum Radio Netherlands in English 0830 GMT 
16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1605090594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hilversum Radio Netherlands </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Dutch minister for overseas development, Jan 
Pronk, has called for aid to be airlifted to Rwanda to provide 
food for the hundreds of thousands of refugees there. 
  Mr. Pronk made his appeal shortly after visiting the Rwandan 
capital, Kigali. The minister called on the United States to 
take the lead in organizing the airlifts. He also called for 
the deployment of an international peacekeeping force to protect 
relief convoys. 
  After his visit to Kigali, Mr. Pronk compared the situation 
in Rwanda with the killing fields of Cambodia, where huge 
numbers of Cambodia's population were slaughtered in a civil war. 

</TEXT>

