<H3> <TI>   Ministry `Strongly Urges' DPRK To Accept Mission </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry `Strongly Urges' DPRK To Accept Mission </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1305121394 Paris LE QUOTIDIEN DE PARIS in French 12 May 94 
p 14 </F>

<F P=103> BR1305121394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris LE QUOTIDIEN DE PARIS </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to a statement by Foreign Ministry 
Spokesman Richard Duque yesterday, France "strongly urges" North 
Korea to accept the new International Atomic Energy Agency 
(IAEA) mission which might be sent within the next couple of 
days to inspect Pyongyang's nuclear facilities, where the 
production of an atomic bomb is suspected to be taking place. 
During this new mission, the inspections at the Yongbyon 
reprocessing plant, where IAEA experts were prevented from 
conducting crucial tests in March, should be continued. 

</TEXT>

