<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Experts Call For Resumption of Nuclear Testing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Experts Call For Resumption of Nuclear Testing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1305131494 Paris LE QUOTIDIEN DE PARIS in French 13 May 94 
p 4 </F>

<F P=103> BR1305131494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris LE QUOTIDIEN DE PARIS </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On Tuesday [10 May], Arthur Paecht, the rapporteur 
of the military programming law, declared that, "according to a 
unanimous recommendation of all experts consulted, the 
resumption of nuclear tests is indispensable." As to the Palen 
test simulation program, it "would not suffice to ensure the 
development of new nuclear charges." The parliamentarian also 
pointed to two other "controversial" issues: "The decision by 
the president of the Republic to keep active the ballistic 
missiles on the Albion plateau" and "the five-year delay in the 
M5 strategic ballistic missile program." 

</TEXT>

