<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kohl Stresses Importance of Federal Europe </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohl Stresses Importance of Federal Europe </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1505112694 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1002 GMT 15 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1505112694 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Duesseldorf (DDP/ADN) -- European unification is a 
question of war and peace in the 21st century, according to 
Chancellor Helmut Kohl. In view of the dramatic changes in 
Germany, Europe, and the world in the past few years, the 
priority now must be to make the political and economic 
unification of Europe irreversible, Kohl said today at the 45th 
master craftsmen's meeting of Duesseldorf Chamber of Trades and 
Crafts. 
  Kohl reaffirmed his support for a federal Europe and firmly 
rejected a central European bureaucracy. It is now primarily a 
question of bringing life to the Maastricht Treaty. A common 
asylum policy and the fight against cross-border crime are 
important issues. 
  Europe is also vital for the German economy, the chancellor 
said. Over 3.5 million jobs in Europe -- about every 10th job -- 
now depend on exports to the other countries of the European 
Union. 
  Kohl pointed out that society needs a lively small business 
sector which takes risks and is a dynamic force. He called upon 
the trades and crafts sector to continue this year to do all it 
can to ensure an adequate supply of training places. The state 
will provide the necessary supplementary funds -- despite the 
budget constraints -- only if they are proved to be insufficient. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-65275 </DOCNO>
