<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kohl Announces EU `Deregulation Offensive' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohl Announces EU `Deregulation Offensive' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1605094494 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0854 GMT 16 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1605094494 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl has 
announced a deregulation offensive in the European Union [EU] 
under the German presidency in the second half of 1994. 
Decisions should be made in Brussels only if they have to be 
made there, Kohl today told a conference of the Central 
Federation of German Commercial Travelers' and Brokers' 
Associations in Bonn. 
  At the same time, the chancellor again supported European 
unity. It is essential not only for the German economy. Europe 
is also insurance against a relapse into chauvinism, ethnic 
conflicts, and religious fanaticism, which are present not just 
in the Balkans. 

</TEXT>

