<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Appoints Undersecretaries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Appoints Undersecretaries </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1305181594 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1515 
GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1305181594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A second Council of Ministers meeting has been 
concluded. At the top of the agenda was the government's 
program and the appointment of the undersecretaries of state. 
Mario De Scalzi reports from Palazzo Chigi [office of the prime 
minister]. 
  [Begin De Scalzi recording] The Council of Ministers has 
appointed 37 undersecretaries: 13 of them come from Forza 
Italia, 12 from the National Alliance, 10 from the Northern 
League, and two from the Christian Democrat Center [CCD]. 
However, the CCD has managed to obtain a very high profile 
appointment that is on a par with a ministry, in other words, 
civil protection which will now be headed by Ombretta Fumagalli 
Carulli. 
  The Council of Ministers also discussed the government's 
program that will be announced on Monday [16 May] by Silvio 
Berlusconi to the Senate and the Chamber of Deputies in order to 
obtain the support of the parliament. 
  So far, there have been few leaks about the contents of the 
program. What is known, is that the program document is at 
least 50 pages long. The main topics will be employment, fiscal 
policy, and privatization. The latter will, however, have to be 
carried out within the framework of the regulations approved by 
the old government that are valid until 30 May. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

