BFN 

  [Text] "If there are any attempts to `take away' confidence 
in the government during the Senate vote, then the Northern 
League will ask for immediate elections." The statement was 
made by Umberto Bossi, the leader of the Northern League, who 
added that the "alliance currently in office was the only one 
capable of providing a democratic government." 
  Bossi said that the opposition would have "to bear the 
responsibility of provoking fresh elections, which would not 
only impose on the country an irresolvable and dangerous crisis, 
but would also go against the will of the the Italian people who 
expressed their will at the ballot box." 

