<H3> <TI>   Ministry To Reduce Personnel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry To Reduce Personnel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1605153794 Frankfurt/Main FRANKFURTER ALLGEMEINE in German 
16 May 94 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> AU1605153794 </F>
<F P=104>  Frankfurt/Main FRANKFURTER ALLGEMEINE </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [DPA report: "Defense Ministry Wants To Shed 1,900 Jobs"] </F>
  [Text] Bonn, 15 May -- Defense Minister Ruehe (Christian 
Democratic Union--CDU) must reduce the number of his employees 
in the Defense Ministry from the present 5,500 to 3,300 in the 
long term, said a Defense Ministry spokesman during the weekend. 
Ruehe wants to eliminate these posts by means of transfers and 
early retirements. There should be no dismissals, said the 
spokesman. Even when Stoltenberg (CDU) was defense minister, 
ways of reducing the number of employees were considered. BILD 
AM SONNTAG has reported on these economization plans, referring 
to a confidential letter Ruehe sent to the Bundestag Defense 
Committee, announcing the personnel reduction. Ten 
subcommittees are to be abolished. 

</TEXT>

