<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Hails Virtues of EU Expansion </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Hails Virtues of EU Expansion </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1605210394 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1800 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1605210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In the opinion of President Martti Ahtisaari, the 
expansion of the European Union [EU] is important from the 
viewpoint of security policy. Addressing the annual meeting of 
the Civil Defense Course Association, Ahtisaari said that the 
expansion of the EU is the most important factor for the 
consolidation of European stability and a vital process for 
joint security. According to Ahtisaari, EU membership creates a 
new kind of action framework for Finland in foreign and security 
policy when it is a member of the chief group influencing 
international politics. Ahtisaari said that he expected much 
from the civic debate preceding the EU referendum, adding that 
the Finns must make it clear to themselves and others in which 
direction they want to take this country. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

