<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Slight Radioactive Water Leak at Nuclear Station </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Slight Radioactive Water Leak at Nuclear Station </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1605183794 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1430 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1605183794 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Repairs on the second unit of the Loviisa nuclear 
power station [on the Finnish south coast] are expected to take 
four days. It was decided to shut down the second unit of the 
nuclear power station when a leak was discovered in the 
reactor's cooling circuit. Slightly radioactive evaporating 
water is dripping through the cooling circuit's valve casing. 
The valve cannot be separated and repaired while the power 
station is running so the unit will be frozen for the duration 
of repairs on the valve. The leak was discovered in the early 
hours of this morning when the station's operators noticed that 
the insulation in the valve casing had become moist. The Center 
for Radiation and Nuclear Safety was informed of the fault in 
the morning. The reason for the leak is not known. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

