<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis, Others Discuss Results of Vienna Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kliridhis, Others Discuss Results of Vienna Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Feissel Briefs Kliridhis </H4>

<F P=102> NC1705085094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 0700 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1705085094 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Gustave Feissel, the UN secretary general's 
alternate special representative, met President Glavkos 
Kliridhis this morning. The purpose of the 45-minute meeting 
was to brief Kliridhis on the Vienna talks at which the United 
Nations gave clarifications to the Turkish side. 
  Answering questions afterward, Feissel said he had prepared 
his report to the secretary general but avoided saying whether 
he had already submitted it. Asked if the report contains any 
ambiguities, Feissel said he does not usually repeat himself. He 
added, however, that the content of the report to be submitted 
to the Security Council is up to the secretary general, just as 
the decision is up to the Security Council. 
  Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis said after the meeting 
that from the briefing it followed that there is no prospect for 
a change in the Turkish stance and that the UN efforts for the 
confidence-building measures have failed. 

</TEXT>

