<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis, Others Discuss Results of Vienna Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kliridhis, Others Discuss Results of Vienna Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Proximity Talks Process `Terminated' </H4>

<F P=102> NC1705123094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1705123094 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government spokesman said the process of 
proximity talks on the confidence-building measures has been 
terminated. Asked if the Cypriot Government considers that the 
process to find a Cyprus solution in general through the method 
of talks has also been terminated, Government Spokesman Ioannis 
Kasoulidhis said the methods followed to date have proven that 
there cannot be progress, due to the lack of political will by 
the Turkish side. 
  Kasoulidhis added that what should be done now is for the 
Security Council members to consider alternative ways to promote 
a Cyprus solution. He added: After the UN secretary general's 
report is submitted, the Security Council might give some time 
for consultations to be held among its members in order to agree 
on the alternative methods to be promoted. He also noted that 
these consultations might include the guarantor powers in Cyprus. 

</TEXT>

