<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cetin Notes UN Failure To Achieve Goals </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cetin Notes UN Failure To Achieve Goals </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1305125294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1305125294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin has said that the 
United Nations, which was established to secure lasting peace in 
the world, had serious failures in achieving its goal during 
this past term. 
  Cetin was addressing the first meeting of the national 
committee set up for the 50th anniversary of the United Nations, 
which will be marked next year. He pointed out that the 
massacre in Bosnia-Herzegovina today is the result of a lack of 
political will on the part of the United Nations. Actually, he 
explained, the will of the United Nations is determined by the 
decision of a few countries. The decision of the five permanent 
members of the UN Security Council becomes the resolution of the 
entire United Nations. Naturally, at times, it is the interests 
of the permanent members that is reflected in a UN resolution or 
in its implementation. Consequently, it would be better to 
criticize the UN decisionmaking mechanism rather than the 
organization and its aims. 
  Cetin pointed out that the phrase "We the peoples of the 
world" has been accepted as the slogan of the 50th anniversary 
celebrations, stressing that this saddles the United Nations 
with great responsibilities that must be fulfilled. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-65394 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu095_q_94008" </HT>


