<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis, Others Discuss Results of Vienna Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kliridhis, Others Discuss Results of Vienna Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kliridhis: Deadlock `Intractable' </H4>

<F P=102> NC1605172394 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1600 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1605172394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis called on the UN 
Security Council to adopt specific alternative ways to implement 
its resolutions on Cyprus. 
  In an interview with ASSOCIATED PRESS, Kliridhis said the 
deadlock became intractable because of the Turkish side's 
continuing intransigence and systematic rejection of UN 
resolutions. The president added that in light of this, the 
Security Council must take an alternative approach in seeking a 
Cyprus solution. 

</TEXT>

